# Architecture

## State Management
**Zustand** = working copy (client state)
- Slices in `src/lib/features/[feature]/[feature]-slice.ts`
- Access via `useAppStore` from `store-provider.tsx`

**React Query** = source of truth (server state)
- Queries: `src/services/[resource]/queries.ts`
- Mutations: `src/services/[resource]/mutations.ts`
- API functions: `src/services/[resource]/[resource]-api.ts`

**Data Flow:**
```
React Query → Zustand (working copy) → User edits → Mutations → React Query refetch
```

## Project Structure
```
src/
├── app/           # Next.js pages
├── components/    # UI components (one per file!)
├── constants/     # Static constants
├── hooks/         # Custom hooks (side effects live here)
├── lib/features/  # Zustand slices
├── providers/     # React context providers
├── services/      # API layer (queries, mutations)
├── types/         # TypeScript types
└── utils/         # Pure utility functions
```

## Naming Conventions
| Type | Convention | Example |
|------|------------|---------|
| Components | PascalCase | `BaseNode` |
| Files | lowercase-with-dashes | `base-node.tsx` |
| Hooks | camelCase with `use` | `useMindmapStore` |
| Props | `[Component]Props` | `BaseNodeProps` |

